## 🧱 Layered Architecture

### 1. Presentation Layer (Frontend)
- Built using **`{{frontendFramework}}`**.
- State management handled by **`{{stateManagement}}`**.
- Handles client-side routing, user input capture, layout rendering, and local state sync.

### 2. Integration & Backend Layer
{{#eq backend "Firebase"}}
- Utilizes a serverless integration pattern using the **Firebase SDK**.
- Security rules are set up at the Firestore/Storage levels to authorize client requests without a separate API server.
{{else}}
- Powered by a **`{{backend}}`** API server.
- Responsible for executing business operations, validating input, checking security contracts, and querying the database.
{{/eq}}

### 3. Data & Storage Layer
{{#eq database "Firestore"}}
- Powered by **Cloud Firestore**, a NoSQL document database.
- Key collections are structured around core domain aggregates (see [BUSINESS_RULES.md](BUSINESS_RULES.md)).
{{else if (eq database "None")}}
- No persistent local or cloud database configured for this stack.
{{else}}
- Powered by **`{{database}}`**.
- Interfaced using custom query helpers or ORMs suited for `{{database}}`.
{{/eq}}

---

{{#eq frontendFramework "Next.js"}}
### Next.js App Router Architecture
- **Routing**: Uses the App Router (`app/`) with file-based routing conventions.
- **Server Components**: Default to React Server Components for data fetching and rendering.
- **Client Components**: Mark interactive components with the `'use client'` directive.
- **Layouts**: Shared layouts in `app/layout.tsx` wrap nested route segments.
- **Data Fetching**: Use `fetch` with caching directives or server-side data access patterns.

---

{{/eq}}
## 🔒 Security & Data Guardrails

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Authentication**: Managed via `{{authProvider}}`.
> - **Input Validation**: All data entering the backend boundary or Firestore database must be validated using runtime validation libraries (e.g., Zod, Valibot, or Joi) on both client and backend.
> - **Cors & Headers**: API requests must strictly adhere to the rules outlined in [API_CONTRACTS.md](API_CONTRACTS.md).

